NORMALISED EXTRACT

Key technical points (implementation-ready):
- Vitest provides test runner functions: test(name, fn), describe(blockName, fn), hooks beforeEach/afterEach/beforeAll/afterAll, and assertion API via expect(value).matcher.
- CLI and scripts: vitest or npx vitest; vitest run for single-run; vitest watch mode for interactive testing; default filename pattern requires ".test." or ".spec.".
- Configuration: vitest reads Vite config by default or a dedicated vitest.config.* file; config options include test.environment (node/jsdom/happy-dom), include/exclude globs, setupFiles, projects support (multiple test configurations).
- Coverage: use vitest run --coverage and coverage providers like @vitest/coverage-v8.

