Details
1. Core API
- test(name: string, fn: () => void | Promise): register a test case; supports async functions returning Promises or using await.
- expect(received).toBe(expected) and other matchers (toEqual, toMatchObject, toHaveBeenCalled, etc.).
- Hooks: beforeEach(fn), afterEach(fn), beforeAll(fn), afterAll(fn) for setup/teardown.

2. CLI usage and scripts
- Typical package.json scripts: "test": "vitest", "coverage": "vitest run --coverage".
- Run single-run (CI): vitest run or npm run test:unit (project-specific script). Watch mode: vitest.

3. Configuration
- vitest.config.{js,ts,mjs,etc} or use test property in vite.config.*.
- Key config options: test.environment, test.include, test.exclude, test.setupFiles, test.globals, test.watch, test.coverage.provider.
- Vitest requires Vite >= 6.0.0 and Node >= 20.0.0.

4. Projects support
- Define multiple test projects inside test config to run different environments in one process; each project may override root, environment, setupFiles.

5. Best practices
- Keep tests deterministic; avoid global state leakage (use setup/teardown hooks).
- Use streaming or targeted tests in CI (use include globs) and enable coverage provider appropriate to runtime.

Supplementary details
- IDE integration: official VS Code extension provides test explorer integration.
- Automatic dependency installation prompt can be disabled with VITEST_SKIP_INSTALL_CHECKS=1.

Reference details (APIs and options)
- test(name: string, fn: () => void | Promise<any>) -> registers test
- describe(name: string, fn: () => void) -> groups tests
- expect(value).toBe(expected) and toEqual, toContain, toMatchObject, toHaveBeenCalled, etc.
- Config: defineConfig({ test: { environment: 'node' | 'jsdom' | 'happy-dom', include: string[], exclude: string[], setupFiles: string[], globals: boolean } })

